---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Glyph from "../components/Glyph.astro";
import CanopyScene from "../components/CanopyScene.astro";
---
<Base title="Colophon" description="What this place is, and how it is made — by hand, with a little help from machines.">
  <article class="page colophon">
    <header class="head">
      <p class="eyebrow"><Glyph name="light" size={18} /> &nbsp;colophon</p>
      <h1>About this place</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose stack">
      <p class="three">
        Enka Kanopi is a canopy — a container for a self in motion, and the
        notes it keeps while remaking its foundations. It is a quiet garden of
        essays about identity, craft, and the body, written for the few who
        care to read slowly and left open for anyone else to overhear. Nothing
        here is for sale and nothing here asks you for anything; it is a place,
        not a funnel.
      </p>

      <div class="rule"></div>

      <h2>How it is made</h2>
      <p>
        By hand, with a little help from machines — and I'd rather say which is
        which than pretend it's all one or all the other. The words are mine.
        The diagrams are <em>drawn</em>, not generated: every wobble in a line
        is a hand's, on purpose, because a ruler-straight version would be
        colder without being any clearer. The site is hand-built static pages —
        warm paper, ink, one poppy-red mark held back for the places the eye
        should land, and a graph-grid so faint you mostly feel it. Machines
        help me build and keep it; they don't do the thinking or the drawing.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name came before the thesis. <em>Kanopi</em> is a canopy — the
        thing that holds. <em>Canopy</em> (木漏れ日) is the light that falls
        through it, legible only because the leaves move. That is the whole of
        it, really: a container, and the light it lets through.
      </p>

      <div class="rule"></div>

      <h2>Colophon proper</h2>
      <ul class="specs">
        <li><span class="k">Words &amp; drawings</span><span class="v">by hand</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">Type</span><span class="v">Newsreader, set for the eye; Caveat, for the margins only</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">Palette</span><span class="v">cream paper, warm ink, one poppy, muted canopy greens</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">Build</span><span class="v">static pages, no tracking, no ask</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">State</span><span class="v"><span class="hand">Volume I · In Formation</span></span></li>
      </ul>

      <p class="byline">
        Written and drawn by <span class="name">Rika Fang</span>.
        <br />
        <a class="link mail" href="mailto:hello@enkakanopi.world">a quiet line, if you'd like one</a>
      </p>
      <!-- SLOT: confirm the contact address before launch. hello@enkakanopi.world is a placeholder pending the domain re-attach. -->

      <div class="scene-foot"><CanopyScene /></div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
<style>
  .colophon { max-width: 44rem; }
  .head { margin-bottom: 1.6rem; }
  .head .eyebrow { display: flex; align-items: center; }
  .head h1 { margin-top: 0.8rem; }
  .three { font-size: 1.22rem; color: var(--ink); }
  .specs { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .specs li {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 11rem 1fr; gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0; border-top: 0.7px solid var(--paper-edge);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
  }
  .specs .k { font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-faint); padding-top: 0.15rem; }
  .specs .v { color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .specs .hand { font-family: var(--hand); font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--canopy-deep); }
  .byline { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-top: 2rem; }
  .byline .name { color: var(--ink); }
  .mail { font-size: 0.98rem; }
  .scene-foot { margin-top: 2.5rem; opacity: 0.85; }
  @media (max-width: 32rem) { .specs li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.1rem; } }
</style>
